'''wgetpaste''' is an extremely simple command-line interface to various online pastebin services.

== Installation ==

Install {{Package|app-text/wgetpaste}}:

{{Emerge|app-text/wgetpaste}}

== Usage ==

Using the {{c|wgetpaste}} command is simple. Presuming bpaste services is selected (which is the default service) to create a paste of the system's Xorg configuration, run the following command:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste /etc/X11/xorg.conf}}

To create a paste of Xorg.conf using the tiny URL service use the <code>-u</code> option:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -u /etc/X11/xorg.conf}}

To set a language for syntax highlighting use the <code>-l</code> option:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -l Bash /etc/bash/bashrc}}

Use <code>-L</code> option to list all available languages, which depends on selected paste service:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -L}}

To paste the entire output of a command, use the <code>-c</code> option. Remember to quote the command:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -c 'emerge -vp musique'}}

== Configuration ==

To list available pastebin services use the <code>-S</code> option:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -S|output=<pre>
Services supported: (case sensitive):
   Name:        | Url:
   =============|=================
   *bpaste      | https://bpaste.net/
    ca          | http://pastebin.ca/
    codepad     | http://codepad.org/
    dpaste      | http://dpaste.com/
    gists       | https://api.github.com/gists
    lugons      | https://paste.lugons.org/
    poundpython | http://paste.pound-python.org/
</pre>}}

To use gists as the pastebin service instead of bpaste (the default) use the <code>-s</code> option with "gists" specified:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste -s gists /etc/X11/xorg.conf}}

== Additional help ==

Additional help can be accessed after wgetpaste has been installed by running the wgetpaste command with the <code>--help</code> option:

{{Cmd|wgetpaste --help}}
